Product name: French Vintage Vellum Vanity Case / Allemand - Arniaud Luggage in a Pale Pigskin Finish and Brass Fittings - Silk Interior and Fitted Mirror
Description:
This super little French vintage vellum vanity case was made by the respected marker Allemand - Arniaud from Marseille (founded in 1840) and would look great in a vintage home as well as being useful storage.  It has a lovely patina of age, brass fittings (including the maker's plaque) and is studded on the sides. Product name: NEW OLD Stock 1950s Swiss Army Backpack, Swiss Army Rucksack, extra straps, Swiss Military Leather Canvas Bag, FHD Rucksack Backpack
Description:
A very special piece from the 1950s: an UNUSED lighter-style Swiss Military or Army backpack or rucksack, made from canvas and dark grey leather. 
**As well as being 'New Old Stock', this bag's additional offering is the three extra leather straps, one on the top and two on the side (see Photos 1 and 3). 
The rucksack's thick outer layer is made from the very popular 'salt and pepper' canvas, which comes across as a mossy, olive green color. 
The shoulder and front straps of the bag are made with strong grey leather. The same leather is also used to line the pockets and top flap. 
The backpack is relatively light to carry but is very, very sturdy. For those interested in using this backpack as a 'carry-on' bag on an aeroplane, this bag is extremely flexible and it can be 'squished' to fit within carry-on measurements. 
Beautifully crafted and hand-stitched, this bag was truly made to last a lifetime. 
CONDITION: As mentioned above, this backpack is 'brand new' old stock from the 1950s. It has never been used and is in the same crisp and clean condition as it was when it was produced around 60 years ago!

Height 21.5" (top to bottom)
Width 16" (facing bag from left to right)

Weight is approx. 1.1kg

This is an old vaghadia Rabari “Ludi”, from kutch Gujarat. This is regional Mochi (shoe maker) influenced embroidery of vaghad in east Bhuj, Gujarat.
The woolen shawls were locally woven by the wool weaver Meghwals, harijans, given to Khatri craft people for tie dyeing and then embroidered by the Rabari Artists.
This is used to give to their daughters on her marriage as Dowry

Description:
Pet Memorial Shadow Box: Dog Memorial Shadow Box, Cat Memorial, Pet Memorial Box, In Memory Of
This high-quality 8x10" pet memorial shadow box is a perfect way to display your cherished pet mementos. Each pet memorial shadow box is custom made to suit the unique bond that you shared.
TO ORDER, copy the following and paste it in the "notes to seller' section when checking out (for your convenience, so you don't have to reference the listing when ordering to make sure all of the relevant information is included:
Pet's name:

FAQ
WHAT IS THE SIZE OF THIS SHADOW BOX?
8" tall, 10" wide, and approx 2.5" deep
DO YOU SELL A LARGER SIZE?
Yes! It is not the exact same shadow box, but it is an 11x14. Listing for the larger item is here:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/483224831/pet-memorial-shadow-box-large-dog
HOW DO I GET MY DOG'S COLLAR, PAW PRINT, AND PICTURE INSIDE?
Two options:
1) I send you the shadow box and you mount the items (select Buyer Mounts)
2) You send the items to me, I mount, and send back to you (select Seller Mounts)*
*If you select 'Seller Mounts,' I will send you instructions on how to get the items to me
* You will need to send the actual print you would like me to use; I do not have the high-quality print capaibilities that these projects merit
DO I GET TO SEE WHAT IT WILL LOOK LIKE?
I will send you a proof of your design prior to completing the shadow box. Please remember to check your Etsy messages to review your proof. 
REGARDING THE PHOTO:
- please send me a high-quality print, no larger than a 4x6 
- I do not recommend having anyone but the pet in the photo, otherwise it seems as though everyone in the photo is being memorialized (although that may be the case and then it is fine)
Please note:
- The backing of the shadow box has a foam layer so you can pin-mount items
- I use a mix of archival-quality tape, hot glue, and pins to mount the items to the back, depending on the materials
- I will arrange the items and vinyl in a way that is visually pleasing - not too busy
- You can provide any layout suggestions, but you can also trust my artistic abilities
Items we can include:
- paw prints
- photo
- collar
- tags
- their favorite biscuit
- their favorite toy

These felt balls are imported from a manufacturer in Nepal that practices fair trade.   This means they pay fair wages, have good working condition, and do not employ child labor.  Azo free dyes are were used to make the balls.

Product name: Edwardian Leather Spats, Goodyear Welt, Ankle Boots, Button Up, Two Tone Gray Black, New Old Stock, Goodyear
Description:
Edwardian Spat Boots, Black & Gray Leather
ca. early 1900s
Hanover. black and gray leather two tone button
up spat shoes.  Stamped on the bottoms "Hanover"
with Goodyear rubber heels and leather soles. They
have pull tabs at the back with "The Hanover Shoe
Co.", which was founded in 1899.  The interiors are
cotton cloth which was common for shoes made
from this time.  Heavy gold/brass stud button ups.
Amazing handsewn soles.  They have never been
worn, purchased from the estate of a former shoe
store owner who must have held onto these beauties
for many, many years.  They are in mint condition.
Black and gray (gray is a bit darker than in photos).
Here is a great link for more info;
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hanover_Shoe
They are not sized, but judging from the insole
measurements think they may work for a mens
8 - 8.5 US with a very narrow width, however best
to verify all measurements well and check out the
link below for size conversions.
Measures; 11 1/8" soles, 10.25" insoles, 3 5/8" width,
5.75" height, 1" heels.
http://www.zappos.com/c/shoe-size-conversion
These are awesome antique boots in amazing condition.
About the only flaw I can see is one of the fabric pull
ups that has torn on the right boot (think it may be
made with silk).
Thanks for viewing.
Happy to check on international shipping cost to your
location.
No Returns on this Item, thanks.
